readme:
Service Usage

This service is used to retrieve metadata about the confirmation of enrolment (COE) data associated with a Visa.
This service accepts a list of COE Ids (retrieved via SV278) and retrieves the associated Visa COE metadata from ICSE.

Service Behaviour

A consumer invokes the service by providing COE Ids.

Service Variants

None

Service Dependencies

This service does not perform any enforcing actions like schema validation, but only passes the request message to ICSE.

Service Composition

Service Flow

An event is generated by the Service Consumer which invokes the RetrieveConfirmationOfEnrolmentDetails service on the ESB.
ESB transforms RetrieveConfirmationOfEnrolmentDetailsReqeust message to RetrieveCOEDetailsRequest message and sends to ICSE.
Use AF1 if ICSE request is timeout.
ICSE returns RetrieveCOEDetailsResponse with COE details or Error message to ESB.
ESB examines the Response Messages within RetrieveCOEDetailsResponse to determine whether there is any error returned by ICSE, if so, use AF2.
ESB transforms RetrieveCOEDetailsResponse message to RetrieveConfirmationOfEnrolmentDetailsResponse message.
Finally ESB returns RetrieveConfirmationOfEnrolmentDetailsResponse with COE details or error message to Service Consumer.
Alternate Flow 1 (AF1)
If the service call was timeout, ESB should return SV281.MSG-E02 to the consumer.
Alternate Flow 2 (AF2)
The following alternate service flow depicts the execution path that takes place when the primary provider (ICSE) raises an error.
ESB transforms ICSE Error into Enterprise Error Message.
ESB returns response with Enterprise Error payload.

Service State Management Decisions

No state management required.
